The Telegraph - Calcutta
 Saturday, October 25, 2003 				 Laughter is the best medicine
																								Laugh and be merry, remember, better the world with a song/ Better the world with a blow in the teeth of a wrong.																								  John Masefield																								Now that the festive season is coming to an end, it is time to bid it adieu cheerfully with laughter. The Assembly of God Church School, in association with Spandan and the Rotary Club of Bhowanipore, presents The Johnny Lever Show, featuring the undisputed monarch of Bollywood comedy, Johnny Lever. Born Johnny Rao, this talented comedians entry into Indian films wasnt easy. His father, an employee of Hindustan Lever, got his son a job in the company. Johnny regaled his bosses with his imitations and was an instant hit. It also earned him the sobriquet of Lever. After a prolonged struggle for a foothold in Bollywood films, success finally came his way. Today he comes to the city with a mission: to raise funds for The Assembly of God Church School (Hindi medium) run for underprivileged children.																								When: Today at 3 pm																								Where: Science City auditorium
